data.author: Chris Lalancette
data.message:
Disable -Werror.

While it is a nice idea, it makes it more difficult to
package for downstream consumers.  In particular, trying
to compile this package on Ubuntu 24.04 fails because
two of the dependencies (tinyxml2 and matplotlib_cpp)
have warnings, and this causes the entire build to fail.

Signed-off-by: Chris Lalancette <clalancette@gmail.com>

data.author: Chris Lalancette
data.message:
Remove pessimizing std::move.

When compiling on gcc 13.2, it complains that the std::move
in these locations are pessimizing, since it can do
copy elision.  Just get rid of the unnecessary std::move
in these cases.

Signed-off-by: Chris Lalancette <clalancette@gmail.com>
